      <abstract>Homogenious reversed martingale can be considered as a sequence
of averages in ergodic theorem for locally finite groups; and vice versa.
In the paper, these relations are used for receiving estimates of
rates of convergence.</abstract>
      <title>Rates of Convergence in Ergodic Theorems for Locally Finite Groups and Reversed Martingales</title>
    </articleInfo>
