      <pdf>j034.pdf</pdf>
      <abstract>A wide class of pulse modulated systems with a stable
linear part is considered. These systems are described
by functional-integral equations with discontinuous
nonlinear operators. With the help of the averaging method
we obtain sufficient frequency conditions  ensuring the absence
of periodic modes whose period contains an integer number
of pulses.</abstract>
      <title>Nonoscillation of Nonlinear Sampled-data Systems</title>
    </articleInfo>
