    <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="36" LastPage="48">
      <pdf>j035.pdf</pdf>
      <abstract>The objective of this paper is to prove that there exists a
small smooth perturbation of a three-dimensional system of
ordinary differential equations with heteroclinic
cycle of the Lorenz type such that in a neighbourhood of the
cycle there is a chaotic locally maximal
invariant set of the perturbed system.
This chaotic set does not contain limit sets of the cycle.</abstract>
      <title>Perturbation of Heteroclinic Cycles of the Lorenz Type</title>
    </articleInfo>
