      <abstract>We consider approximate solutions of parabolic equations
on an infinite time interval obtained from a sequence of
discretizations such that their time and space steps tend
to 0. Conditions are given under which these solutions tend
to exact ones. Rate of convergence is estimated.</abstract>
      <title>Limit Shadowing and Discretizations of Parabolic Equations</title>
